content: Had a pivotal meeting with urban planners. They're interested in how our tech can help with city planning. We're now discussing real-time data integration for better urban development. Also, Xander's personality tweaks are starting to show—he's more engaging now.

Just wrapped up a session where we adjusted Xander's responses to be more empathetic. It's about making tech feel more human, right? Also, the eco-routes are now part of a city initiative to reduce congestion and pollution. Feels like we're making a real difference.
